fit <- density(globalpoints$points,from=0)

Interpolate density for our league

# get height for our league by interpolation
  df_densinterpolate<-rbind(df_dens,df_our)%>%
        arrange(points)%>%
        mutate(yhat=na.approx(y))%>%
  filter(Name!="")

3 Create plots

3.1 Global points on histogram

Prepare data

# get height for our league by interpolation
  df_densinterpolate_names_right<-df_densinterpolate%>%mutate(lab=paste(33-row_number(),Name))%>%filter(row_number()>10)
  df_densinterpolate_names_left<-df_densinterpolate%>%mutate(lab=paste(33-row_number(),Name))%>%
    filter(row_number()<11,row_number()>7)
    # density estimate
  fit <- density(globalpoints$points,from=0)
  df_dens<-data.frame(points=fit$x,y=fit$y,Name="")
  # get height for our league
  df_densinterpolate<-rbind(df_dens,df_our)%>%arrange(points)%>%mutate(yhat=na.approx(y))%>%filter(Name!="")
  df_densinterpolate_names_right<-df_densinterpolate%>%mutate(lab=paste(33-row_number(),Name))%>%filter(row_number()>10)
  df_densinterpolate_names_left<-df_densinterpolate%>%mutate(lab=paste(33-row_number(),Name))%>%
    filter(row_number()<11,row_number()>7)

Create plot

  # create plot  
  showtext_auto()
ggplot()+
    geom_area(df_dens,mapping=aes(x=points,y=y),fill="#999999")+
    geom_point(df_densinterpolate,mapping=aes(x=points,y=yhat),colour="#2c6142")+
    geom_text_repel(df_densinterpolate_names_right,mapping=aes(x=points,y=yhat,label=lab),segment.size=1, nudge_x =150, direction = "y", hjust = "left",max.overlaps = Inf,colour="#2c6142",family="bell")+
    geom_text_repel(df_densinterpolate_names_left,mapping=aes(x=points,y=yhat,label=lab),segment.size=1, nudge_x =-150, direction = "y", hjust = "right",max.overlaps = Inf,colour="#2c6142",family="bell")+
    xlim(0,3000)+ylim(0,0.0015)+
    theme_minimal()+labs(x="Total points",y="Density",title="#EconTwitterFPL 2020/21 - Final Total Score Ranking ")+
    geom_curve(aes(x = 700 ,y = 0.00025, xend =900, yend =0.0001),colour = "#999999",size=0.75, curvature = +0.2,
               arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.02, "npc")))+
    annotate("text", x =  700 ,y =  0.000295, size=4,colour = "#5b5b5b",label ="Global FPL distribution",family="bell")+
    theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#fff8e0"),text=element_text(family="bell",color="black"),
          plot.title = element_text(size=25,hjust=0.5,family="bell"),
          axis.text = element_text(family="bell",color="black"))

  ggsave("fig1.png")
## Saving 7 x 5 in image

3.2 Variance plot

Data prep

    # calculate variance
df_var<-econtwitterfpl%>%mutate(p=GP-TC)%>%group_by(Name)%>%summarise(sd=sd(p))%>%
       arrange(sd)%>%mutate(rank=row_number())
    df_plotdata<-merge(econtwitterfpl,df_var,by="Name")%>%arrange(sd)%>%mutate(p=GP-TC,
    label=paste(rank," ",Name," ","(SD=",round(sd,2),")",sep=""))

Create plot

ggplot(df_plotdata)+
      geom_density_ridges(aes(x=p,y=reorder(label,-sd)),
                           fill="#4b8259",color="#4b8259", alpha = .8) +
      theme_ridges() + xlim(0,135)+
      theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(),axis.text = element_text(family = "bell"),
            axis.title =element_text(family = "bell",hjust=0.5 ),
            plot.title =element_text(family = "bell",hjust=0.5 ),
            plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#fff8e0"))+
      labs(title="#EconTwitterFPL 2020/21 - Final Lowest Variance Ranking ",x="Points")
## Picking joint bandwidth of 6.96

# save      
ggsave("fig2.png")
## Saving 7 x 5 in image
## Picking joint bandwidth of 6.96

3.3 Team support rank

Data prep

    # calculate variance
    df_teams<-econtwitterfpl%>%filter(GW=="GW38")%>%select(OP,Team)%>%
      group_by(Team)%>%summarise(points=mean(OP),n=n())%>%mutate(r=round(points),
                                                                 Team=paste(Team," (N=",n,")",sep="" ))

Create chart

ggplot(df_teams,aes(x=reorder(Team,points),y=points))+
      geom_bar(stat="identity",fill="#4b8259")+
      geom_text(aes(label=r),nudge_y=70,family="bell")+
      coord_flip()+
      theme_minimal()+
      labs(y="Average points",x=" ",title="#EconTwitterFPL 2020/21 -  points by supported team")+
      theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#fff8e0"),text=element_text(family="bell",color="black"),
            plot.title = element_text(size=25,hjust=0.5,family="bell"),
            axis.text = element_text(family="bell",color="black"))

    set.seed(2048)
